We can equate the expressions for $A_n$ and $B_n$:
\begin{align*}
704 \cdot \frac{1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n}{1 - \frac{1}{2}} &= 1984 \cdot \frac{1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n}{1 + \frac{1}{2}} \\
\Rightarrow \qquad 704 \cdot \frac{1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n}{\frac{1}{2}} &= 1984 \cdot \frac{1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n}{\frac{3}{2}} \\
\Rightarrow \qquad 704 \cdot \left(1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n\right) &= 1984 \cdot \left(1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n\right) \cdot \frac{3}{4}.
\end{align*}

We can set $A_n = B_n$ and solve for $n$:
\begin{align*}
704 \cdot \frac{1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n}{1 - \frac{1}{2}} &= 1984 \cdot \frac{1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n}{1 + \frac{1}{2}} \\
\Rightarrow\qquad 704 \cdot \left(1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n\right) &= 1984 \cdot \left(1 - \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^n\right) \cdot \frac{2}{3} \\
\Rightarrow\qquad 704 &= 1984 \cdot \frac{2}{3} \\
\Rightarrow\qquad 6 &= 7 \\
\Rightarrow\qquad \boxed{\text{There is no solution.}}
